caption:
Bob Dylan’s solo music catalog has been surging in streams thanks to the new biopic ‘A Complete Unknown.’

From the first week of October through the end of November, Dylan’s catalog averaged about 7.7 million on-demand official U.S. streams per week, according to Luminate. In the Dec. 27-Jan. 2 tracking week (the first week after the film was released on Dec. 25), his catalog raked to 20.2 million streams. In the latest tracking week (Jan. 3-9), his catalog earned 18.8 million streams.

Take a look at Bob Dylan’s weekly streams since October, and tap the link in bio for details.
